# UBSan special-case (ignore) list.
#
# simdjson's SIMD fallbacks call __builtin_clz/__builtin_ctz which, on some
# inputs, are invoked with a zero argument. That is well-defined for simdjson's
# usage but UBSan's `builtin` check (part of -fsanitize=undefined) reports
# "passing zero to clz()/ctz()". This is a pre-existing UPSTREAM issue in
# simdjson, not in our code (see PLAN.md phase-9 carry-forward and the phase-6
# reviewer note).
#
# We suppress it at compile time via -fsanitize-ignorelist=<this file> (the
# ignorelist mechanism, preferred over a runtime UBSAN_OPTIONS suppression):
# any source whose path matches *simdjson* is not instrumented. FetchContent
# places simdjson under build*/_deps/simdjson-src/..., which matches.
#
# `src:` entries with no [section] header apply to all enabled sanitizers.
src:*simdjson*
